As expected the absolute values after standardization of weighted signature (stand.fun(weightedSignature$GRAMD1B)) is same as those of standardized expression values (stand.fun(expressionData$GRAMD1B)). The only difference comes from sign of the beta coefficient which is negative for GRAMD1B

os<-data.frame()
pfs<-data.frame()
temp<-data.frame()

combinations<-c("", 
                "+as.character(Stage_binary)")

for (combination in combinations) {
  #Add TIL score if tissue = Skin, otherwise, omit
    os_formula<-paste0("survival_d_ltrc~Signature",combination, collapse = "")
    pfs_formula<-paste0("survival_rd_ltrc~Signature",combination, collapse = "")
  #Overall survival
  fit = coef(summary(coxph(as.formula(os_formula), data=clinicalData)))
  mid  = fit[1,c("exp(coef)")]
  low  = exp(fit[1,c("coef")]-
              qnorm(.975)*fit[1,c("se(coef)")])                   
  high = exp(fit[1,c("coef")]+
              qnorm(.975)*fit[1,c("se(coef)")])  
  pval = fit[1,c("Pr(>|z|)")]
  temp["Signature",c("Group", "Hazard_Ratio","Lower_HazardRatio","Upper_HazardRatio","p_value")] = c(paste0("GRAMD1B",combination, collapse = ""),mid,low,high,pval)
  os<-rbind(os, temp)
  
  #Progression-free survival
  fit = coef(summary(coxph(as.formula(pfs_formula), data=clinicalData)))
  mid  = fit[1,c("exp(coef)")]
  low  = exp(fit[1,c("coef")]-
              qnorm(.975)*fit[1,c("se(coef)")])                   
  high = exp(fit[1,c("coef")]+
              qnorm(.975)*fit[1,c("se(coef)")])  
  pval = fit[1,c("Pr(>|z|)")]
  temp["Signature",c("Group", "Hazard_Ratio","Lower_HazardRatio","Upper_HazardRatio","p_value")] = c(paste0("GRAMD1B",combination, collapse = ""),mid,low,high,pval)
  pfs<-rbind(pfs, temp)
}

             "GRAMD1B+\nStage (II vs III)"), levels=c("GRAMD1B", 
             "GRAMD1B+\nStage (II vs III)"))
